            "abstractNote": "The taxonomy of the genus Plecotus in the Iberian Peninsula and the Canary Islands was studied based on 129 specimens organized in several samples, including P.auritus, P. austriacus austriacus, P. austriacus christiei and P. teneriffae. Univariate and multivariate mo hometric analyses indicated the existence of three different groups : P. austriacus, P. aurilus auritus and a population of P. auritus from the south of the Iberian Peninsula, including P. teneriffae from the Canary Islands. With a discriminant analysis for a priori groups, the maximum of matrix classification (94,4%) was obtained from 9 characters of the 20 which were simultaneously considered. The Plecotus population from the south of the Iberian Peninsula seems to be closer to P. auritus auritus and it should be regarded as a new subspecies. Its geographical distribution coincides with areas of high altitude in the Supramediterranean Level.",
